Name: ethanol production from sugar beet molasses | ethanol, without water, in 95% solution state, from fermentation | EN15804GD, U
Category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals
Description: The process is similar to that of sugarbeet-to-ethanol. The production of syrup from stillage includes pre-concentration and concentration. The syrup is 58% dry matter and is used as animal feed.
